  <h2><a href="/articles/2006/02/13/growlsvnnotifier-in-the-flesh">GrowlSvnNotifier in the flesh</a></h2>
<p class="auth">Posted by kev
<span class="typo_date" title="Mon, 13 Feb 2006 22:06:00 GMT">Mon, 13 Feb 2006 22:06:00 GMT</span></p>
<p>So, I haven&#8217;t had time to figure out the bugs interacting with <a href="http://dnssd.rubyforge.org/wiki/wiki.pl">DNS-SD</a> and <a href="http://growl.info/">Growl</a>, but I&#8217;ve tested this on a few systems now and it seems to do the job. I&#8217;ve changed the code to look for Bonjour enabled Skype (start it up from the Window->Bounjour menu on Mac) since we all use it at the office.</p>

<p>It requires DNS-SD from cvs (it compiles cleanly on everything I&#8217;ve tried it on) and <a href="http://segment7.net/projects/ruby/growl/">ruby-growl</a> which is avaliable as a gem. </p>

<p>Just shove the script in as post-commit in your svn repository and make sure your svn instance has permission to run it. On the client side (Growl) end, enable &#8220;Listen for incomming notifications&#8221; and &#8220;Allow remote application registration&#8221; under Network. Feel free to set a password both in Growl and using the UDP_PASSWORD constant in the script.</p>

<p>MIT license, no warranty or fault on this end yada yada.</p>

<p>Feel free to report bugs, problems, and ESPECIALLY success stories here.</p>

<div class="typocode"><div class="codetitle">post-commit</div><pre><code class="typocode_ruby "><span class="comment">#!/usr/bin/env ruby</span>
<span class="ident">require</span> <span class="punct">'</span><span class="string">dnssd</span><span class="punct">'</span>
<span class="ident">require</span> <span class="punct">'</span><span class="string">rubygems</span><span class="punct">'</span>
<span class="ident">require</span> <span class="punct">'</span><span class="string">ruby-growl</span><span class="punct">'</span>
<span class="ident">require</span> <span class="punct">'</span><span class="string">timeout</span><span class="punct">'</span>

<span class="keyword">module </span><span class="module">GrowlSvnNotifier</span>
  <span class="constant">BROWSE_TIME</span> <span class="punct">=</span> <span class="number">5</span> <span class="comment"># seconds</span>
  <span class="comment"># Set this to the password configured on growl if you've got one</span>
  <span class="constant">UDP_PASSWORD</span> <span class="punct">=</span> <span class="constant">nil</span> 

  <span class="keyword">class </span><span class="class">Notifier</span>
    <span class="keyword">class </span><span class="punct">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class="constant">self</span>

      <span class="keyword">def </span><span class="method">run</span>
        <span class="ident">commit_message</span> <span class="punct">=</span> `<span class="ident">svnlook</span> <span class="ident">log</span> <span class="punct">-</span><span class="ident">r</span><span class="comment">#{ARGV[1]} #{ARGV[0]}`</span>
        <span class="ident">author</span> <span class="punct">=</span> `<span class="ident">svnlook</span> <span class="ident">author</span> <span class="punct">-</span><span class="ident">r</span><span class="comment">#{ARGV[1]} #{ARGV[0]}`</span>
        <span class="ident">find_growl_clients</span><span class="punct">.</span><span class="ident">each</span> <span class="keyword">do</span> <span class="punct">|</span><span class="ident">host</span><span class="punct">|</span>
          <span class="ident">g</span> <span class="punct">=</span> <span class="constant">Growl</span><span class="punct">.</span><span class="ident">new</span> <span class="ident">host</span><span class="punct">,</span> <span class="punct">&quot;</span><span class="string">SVN Notifier</span><span class="punct">&quot;,</span> <span class="punct">[&quot;</span><span class="string">SVN Notification</span><span class="punct">&quot;],</span> 
                              <span class="constant">nil</span><span class="punct">,</span> <span class="constant">UDP_PASSWORD</span>
          <span class="ident">g</span><span class="punct">.</span><span class="ident">notify</span> <span class="punct">&quot;</span><span class="string">SVN Notification</span><span class="punct">&quot;,</span> <span class="punct">&quot;</span><span class="string">Revision #<span class="expr">#{ARGV[1]}</span></span><span class="punct">&quot;,</span> 
                    <span class="punct">&quot;</span><span class="string">Commited by <span class="expr">#{author}</span>:<span class="escape">\n</span><span class="expr">#{commit_message}</span></span><span class="punct">&quot;</span>
        <span class="keyword">end</span>
      <span class="keyword">end</span>

      <span class="keyword">def </span><span class="method">find_growl_clients</span>
        <span class="ident">hosts</span> <span class="punct">=</span> <span class="punct">[]</span>
        <span class="ident">timeout</span><span class="punct">(</span><span class="constant">BROWSE_TIME</span><span class="punct">)</span> <span class="keyword">do</span>
          <span class="constant">DNSSD</span><span class="punct">.</span><span class="ident">browse!</span><span class="punct">('</span><span class="string">_skype._tcp</span><span class="punct">')</span> <span class="keyword">do</span> <span class="punct">|</span><span class="ident">b</span><span class="punct">|</span>
            <span class="ident">hosts</span> <span class="punct">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class="ident">resolve_ip</span><span class="punct">(</span><span class="ident">b</span><span class="punct">.</span><span class="ident">name</span><span class="punct">,</span> <span class="ident">b</span><span class="punct">.</span><span class="ident">type</span><span class="punct">,</span> <span class="ident">b</span><span class="punct">.</span><span class="ident">domain</span><span class="punct">)</span>
          <span class="keyword">end</span>
        <span class="keyword">end</span>
      <span class="keyword">rescue</span> <span class="constant">TimeoutError</span>
        <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="ident">hosts</span>
      <span class="keyword">end</span>

      <span class="keyword">def </span><span class="method">resolve_ip</span><span class="punct">(</span><span class="ident">name</span><span class="punct">,</span> <span class="ident">type</span><span class="punct">,</span> <span class="ident">domain</span><span class="punct">)</span>
        <span class="constant">DNSSD</span><span class="punct">.</span><span class="ident">resolve!</span><span class="punct">(</span><span class="ident">name</span><span class="punct">,</span> <span class="ident">type</span><span class="punct">,</span> <span class="ident">domain</span><span class="punct">)</span> <span class="keyword">do</span> <span class="punct">|</span><span class="ident">r</span><span class="punct">|</span>
          <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="ident">r</span><span class="punct">.</span><span class="ident">target</span>
        <span class="keyword">end</span>
      <span class="keyword">end</span>

    <span class="keyword">end</span>
  <span class="keyword">end</span>  
<span class="keyword">end</span>

<span class="constant">GrowlSvnNotifier</span><span class="punct">::</span><span class="constant">Notifier</span><span class="punct">.</span><span class="ident">run</span></code></pre></div>

<h3>Update</h3>

<p>Damien Tanner has <a href="http://mongoo.se/articles/2006/02/14/growl-notification-of-svn-commits">modified the GrowlSvnNotifier for remote use</a> (and is using it on DreamHost) by rewriting <code>find_growl_clients</code> to return an array of ip addresses instead of running through and detecting bonjour instances. This is great for static ips as well as remote use. Good stuff.</p>

  
