  <h2><a href="/articles/2006/02/11/acts-as-threaded">Acts As Threaded</a></h2>
<p class="auth">Posted by kev
<span class="typo_date" title="Sat, 11 Feb 2006 17:42:00 GMT">Sat, 11 Feb 2006 17:42:00 GMT</span></p>
<p><a href="http://www.railtie.net/">Bob Silva</a> who has been a <a href="http://dev.rubyonrails.org/ticket/3158">monster</a> <a href="http://dev.rubyonrails.org/ticket/3743">on</a> the <a href="http://dev.rubyonrails.org">Rails Trac System</a> and core list as of late has just released a screencast of his newest toy, <a href="http://www.railtie.net/articles/2006/02/05/rails-acts_as_threaded-plugin">acts_as_threaded</a>.</p>

<p>Acts as threaded allows you to created threaded entries (like a forum) easily and without the hassle of dealing with acts_as_nested_set and such.</p>

<p>Go check it out. Thanks alot Bob! Good work.</p>

  
